The Telegraph - Calcutta : Entertainment

 Rat-a-tat

 It rsquo;s a rat rsquo;s life, no doubt, but Remy is happy to have achieved all that he could dream of (in the kitchen). The Ratatouille rat hits town today

 Remy the rat in Ratatouille

 What is that one quote you would like to share with your audiences? 

 Ive always believed, with hard work and a little bit of luck, its only a matter of time before Im discovered!

 If you were given an opportunity to be reborn what would you prefer to be born as?

 Remy the RAT, cause I have achieved all that I could ever dream of.

 Remy, you are the hero of this film, but on the whole people dont get all warm and fuzzy when they think about rats. Did that worry you? 

 Yes, most people, if they see a rat, theyre scared of it. So now what? Well, there have been many characters in film history like Mickey Mouse or Jerry from Tom and Jerry or my latest neighbour Stuart Little who have been adored by millions. And here is me, the sweet little me, who can cook, read a book and be loved.

 How close is your character to a human?

 Well, the director (Brad Bird) has surely tried to bring in a whole lot of human element in me. They did take some theatrical liberties on me.

 Any stunts in the film?

 Yes, Remy walks on two legs, for example, but its not just random, it comes from his character. If youre a rat and want to become a chef, youre sure as heck not going to walk around on all fours in the kitchen, right? One better get thinking of where ones paws could be touching? The stunt did make me feel taller but my back toes hurt for a week after that.

 What do you like most about your character Remy? 

 Hmm!!! ThinkingWhat I love most about the character is that he doesnt settle. Hes always looking to the horizon for a new experience. Of course, thats why hes the skinniest of all the rats because he only wants to take in the very best. He always wants something more from life, and I like that about him.

 What about Patton Oswalt? How does it feel to have him donate towards your vocal being?

 Well, for Oswalt being offered a Disney film was like a dream coming true, as it was for me. I think he gives the film a special comic edge which comes from his outrageous routines on radio. His voice brings out the best in me, doing full justice to my character. Well, you will have to watch Ratatouille to believe this.

 How is the movie connected to food?

 Im a big foodie myself and a lot of people in this movie are foodies too, so that was a lot of fun. The food itself in this movie is a landscape of deliciousness that is just so artistically done. I have actually had a whole lot of experience with food and chefs and its been wonderful when you get to do what you love to do cooking and eating, in my case.

 Would you give Linguini all the credit for your success story? 

 Yes indeed, Remys dreams would never get a chance to come true if it werent for Linguini (voice: Lou Romano), the lowly garbage boy at Gusteaus who discovered my talents and found them changing his own fortune. Although we started out together out of mutual desperation Linguini needing to hang onto his job and me hoping to finally get a chance to work in a real live restaurant kitchen we slowly became buddies who learn they can truly count on one another. I have seriously found a bum-chum-pal in Linguini.

 How was the whole Paris experience? 

 Great! I simply love going on to the roof and taking a fresh breath of air which is rich with the fragrance of the best cheese, wine and pastries in the world.

 We understand you and your culinary skills have been greatly influenced by Chef Auguste Gusteau ; please enlighten your fans on this one?

 Auguste (voice: Brad Garrett) has changed my life. His mantra anyone can cook is going to be a lifelong inspiration for me. His cookbook Anyone Can Cook inspired me to become a chef. His spirit will always live on in his recipes and in my imagination. He is and will always be my soulmate and my counsellor.

 What about your brother Emile? 

 Emile (voice: Peter Sohn) is a lover of life and all things whether they are edible or not. He is my best buddy and a perfect audience for my culinary delights.

 Finally, where do you see yourself compared to other human chefs?

 Well, I wouldnt like to flaunt my culinary skills but seriously, my remarkable sense of smell and genius of combining flavours puts me head and shoulders above most human chefs.




